decision_conditions: Condition 92 which reads: No development shall be occupied until confirmation has been provided that either:- all water network upgrades required to accommodate the additional flows to serve the development have been completed; or - a development and infrastructure phasing plan has been agreed with Thames Water to allow development to be occupied.Where a development and infrastructure phasing plan is agreed no occupation shall take place other than in accordance with the agreed housing and infrastructure phasing plan.Reason - The development may lead to no/ low water pressure and network reinforcement works are anticipated to be necessary to ensure that sufficient capacity is made available to accommodate additional demand anticipated from the new development" The developer can request information to support the discharge of this condition by visiting the Thames Water website at thameswater.co.uk/preplanning.Is replaced with:No development in any Phase or Development Plot shall be occupied until confirmation has been provided that either:- all water network upgrades required to accommodate the additional flows to serve the development  in any Phase or Development Plot have been completed; or - a development and infrastructure phasing plan has been agreed with Thames Water to allow the development in any Phase or Development Plot to be occupied.Where a development and infrastructure phasing plan is agreed no occupation shall take place other than in accordance with the agreed housing and infrastructure phasing plan.Reason - The development may lead to no/ low water pressure and network reinforcement works are anticipated to be necessary to ensure that sufficient capacity is made available to accommodate additional demand anticipated from the new development" The developer can request information to support the discharge of this condition by visiting the Thames Water website at thameswater.co.uk/preplanning.
description: Non Material Amendment to planning permission 20/02942/FUL to remove Condition 17 and amend the wording of Condition 92.
